cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI 

This paper focuses on privacy-preserving visual recognition, which involves computer vision and privacy concerns. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses adversarial training, which is a common technique in the field of computer security, suggesting that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a likely sub-category. The paper proposes a unique framework that optimizes the trade-off between target task performance and privacy budgets, which involves machine learning and optimization, indicating that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category. The paper also involves video processing, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia), and privacy protection, which involves AI techniques, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible sub-category.
